"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349775","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-28","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office is responsible for coordinating cross-Government positions at the UN on the rights of older people. Our long-held position, shared with EU partners, is that the focus should be on the implementation of the existing Human Rights framework, which applies to all individuals without distinction.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2015-07-28T16:25:26.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349775/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349775/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349775/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-10","Human Rights: Older People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will take steps to include the rights of older people in his Department's work on human rights and consider how such rights may be protected globally.","false","Biography information for Heidi Alexander","Lewisham East","Heidi Alexander","1791"
