"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349780","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-15","<p /> <p>Last year the Department undertook an initial feasibility assessment of a voucher scheme to pay Winter Fuel Payments directly to energy providers. It showed that there would be significant additional administrative complexities and costs to the energy providers which were likely to directly increase the fuel bills for all customers and we expected that a significant number of the most vulnerable pensioners would lose out by not redeeming their voucher.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-15T15:18:03.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349780/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349780/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349780/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-10","Winter Fuel Payments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment his Department has made of the feasibility of paying winter fuel allowance payments directly to energy providers; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","1798"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349781","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-15","<p>Seal conservation is a devolved issue so I can only respond with respect to England. Approximately 85% of the UK seal population is in Scotland and the Scottish Government has its own legislation concerning the protection of seals.</p><p>Seals in England are primarily protected by the Conservation of Seals Act 1970. Under this Act, it is an offence to take or kill common and grey seals out of season or to use certain methods to kill or take, unless permitted to do so by a licence issued under the Act.</p><p>Fishermen are only permitted to kill or take seals in limited circumstances, without the need for a licence, to protect their fishing equipment or fish therein if the seal is in the vicinity of the equipment at that time.</p><p>The Conservation of Seals Act 1970 strikes a proportionate balance between the conservation and welfare of the seals and the needs of those impacted by individual problem seals. We have no plans to review this legislative protection.</p><p>There is no evidence to suggest that the limited local control of seals permitted in England is having an adverse effect on the conservation status of the UK seal population as a whole.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2015-06-15T11:26:38.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349781/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349781/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349781/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-10","Seals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if she will take steps to require fishermen to be licensed in order to slaughter seals that threaten their fishing stocks.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","1799"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349782","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-23","<p>My Rt. Hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport places great importance on the Hague Convention for the Protection of Cultural Property in the Event of Armed Conflict and will make the case to ministerial colleagues for introducing the necessary legislation to allow UK ratification at the earliest opportunity.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-06-23T15:40:22.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349782/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349782/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349782/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-10","UN Convention for Protection of Cultural Property in Event of Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what his policy is on UK ratification of the 1954 Hague Convention on the Protection of Cultural Property in the Event of Armed Conflict.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","1800"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349783","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-17","<p>The exact extent of the North in the context of the Northern Powerhouse is not prescribed by the Government.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2015-06-17T15:10:19.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349783/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349783/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349783/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-10","Regional Planning and Development: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what geographic area is covered by the Government's Northern Powerhouse initiative.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","1801"
