"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349785","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-17","<p>Reporting on the progress made by the North East Local Enterprise Partnership on delivering their Strategic Economic Plan is a matter for the Local Enterprise Partnership and they published a review in March 2015 which is available at: <a href="http://nelep.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/North-East-LEP-Annual-Review-2014-to-2015lr.pdf" target="_blank">http://nelep.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/North-East-LEP-Annual-Review-2014-to-2015lr.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2015-06-17T15:13:33.05Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349785/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349785/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349785/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-10","Local Enterprise Partnerships: North East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what progress the North East Local Enterprise Partnership has made on each of its principal functions since its formation.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","1803"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349786","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-17","The review reinforces the case for EU reform. This includes a broader and deeper Single Market, greater competitiveness and flexibility, better (and less) regulation and more transparent and accountable institutions and processes.","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2015-06-17T14:02:45.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349786/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349786/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349786/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-10","EU Reform","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what key issues relating to EU reform the Government has identified from the Balance of Competences review.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","1804"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349787","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-17","<p>The Prime Minister, my right hon. Friend the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron), has already been clear about areas where he wants to see reform. These include: reforming welfare; increasing economic competitiveness to create jobs and growth; protecting Britain's interests outside the euro; and dealing with the idea of Ever Closer Union – which may be right for others but is not right for Britain.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2015-06-17T14:03:39.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349787/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349787/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349787/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-10","EU Reform","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what his objectives are for negotiations with representatives of the EU and EU member state governments on EU reform.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","1805"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349788","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-24","<p>The Department, working with Highways England, is in the process of procuring consultants to undertake the Northern Trans-Pennine Strategic Study, which includes consideration of the A69. It is anticipated that this will report by the end of 2016. I have recently written to MPs and council leaders whose constituencies or local authorities are directly affected by the strategic studies informing them of the studies’ imminent formal commencement.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-06-24T11:30:59.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349788/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349788/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349788/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-10","A69","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what timescale he has planned for the completion of the feasibility study of the upgrading of the A69.","false","Biography information for John Stevenson","Carlisle","John Stevenson","1814"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349789","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-24","<p>Prior to the publication of the Intercity West Coast Invitation to Tender there will be a consultation on the specification of the next franchise. This consultation exercise will help to inform the development of the Invitation to Tender and I would welcome my Hon Friend to submit his ideas for Carlisle station.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-06-24T11:35:57.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349789/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349789/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349789/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-10","Carlisle Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will include a requirement to upgrade Carlisle station in the next invitation to tender for the West Coast Mainline franchise.","false","Biography information for John Stevenson","Carlisle","John Stevenson","1815"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349790","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-15","<p>The RAF will reach its Strategic Defence and Security Review 2010 manpower targets through a managed programme of reductions. This includes the retirement of platforms such as Tornado GR4 and Sentinel and their associated squadrons. The reductions will affect a broad range of ranks across the RAF and will be achieved through the previous two tranches of redundancy and forecast exits.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-06-15T15:54:51.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349790/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349790/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349790/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-10","Air Force","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 9 June 2015 to Question 1248, which squadrons will be reduced in size as a result of the reduction in personnel planned between 2015-16 and 2019-20; and how he plans to reduce personnel numbers in each rank of the RAF in order to achieve that reduction.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","1816"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349791","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-15","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 9 June 2015 to Question 1245 to the hon. Member for North Durham (Mr Jones).</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","1634 ; 1645 ; 1674","2015-06-15T15:48:54.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349791/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349791/answer","HOC 1645 9 June 2015.doc","HOC 1645 9 June 2015.doc","Ministry of Defence: Public Expenditure","Ministry of Defence: Public Expenditure","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349791/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-10","Ministry of Defence: Cost Effectiveness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to his Answer of 9 June 2015 to Question 1245, by how much he plans to reduce his Department's expenditure on (a) consultants and (b) overtime and travel; and how he plans to re-profile equipment and infrastructure spending.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","1818"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349792","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-15","<p>Ministers in the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS) have not had discussions with the European Commission on dumping of steel products in the EU by China and Turkey.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>However, BIS officials are in regular contact with Commission officials responsible for anti-dumping investigations, and have had discussions with them last and this year about a specific case of alleged dumping, and related matters, in the steel market. The most recent contact took place on 9 February.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-06-15T16:32:46.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349792/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349792/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349792/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-10","EU External Trade: Iron and Steel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what discussions he has had with the European Commission on dumping of steel products in EU markets by China and Turkey.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","1820"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349793","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-15","<p>I met President Silanyo of Somaliland and other Somaliland Ministers in London in October 2014, at the UK-Somaliland Trade &amp; Investment Forum, where I discussed Somaliland’s economic growth, political landscape, security, and development co-operation. HMG officials regularly meet members of the Somaliland Government and work closely with them on shared objectives. The British Ambassador to Somalia most recently visited Hargeisa in late May and met President Silanyo.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2015-06-15T13:24:11.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349793/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349793/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349793/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-10","Somaliland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, when he last met representatives of the government of Somaliland.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","1821"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349794","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-15","<p>We are not able to estimate accurately the numbers of British nationals in countries to which we advise against travel or where we have restricted or no representation. Our ability to provide consular assistance to British Nationals in those countries is also limited. However we will, where we can, support British Nationals who require consular assistance, as we have for those that have left Yemen following the Saudi-led military action, which began in March 2015.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-06-15T15:50:50.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349794/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349794/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349794/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-10","British Nationals Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent estimate he has made of the number of British citizens in (a) Yemen, (b) Syria, (c) Libya, (d) Somalia and (e) Iraq.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","1822"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349795","Home Office","false","2015-06-22","<p>The Welsh Extremism and Counter Terrorism Unit does receive funding from the Counter Terrorism Policing Grant. The Home Office does not publically provide a breakdown of the Counter Terrorism Policing Grant by region or capability for security reasons.</p><p>In the Spending Round 2013, specific funding for counter-terrorism was protected to 2015-16. A Written Ministerial Statement (WMS) in December 2013 confirmed that the police CT resource budget would be at least £564 million for 2014-15. A WMS in December 2014 confirmed at least the same amount would be available for 2015-16. In addition, HM Treasury has increased funding in 2015-16 for counter terrorism policing by a further £14.9 million to strengthen our capabilities in response to the increased threat from terrorism.</p><p>Whilst budgets have been set for 2015-16, budgets for future years will be determined after the upcoming Spending Review.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2015-06-22T14:52:46.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349795/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349795/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349795/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-06-10","Welsh Extremism and Counter Terrorism Unit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what resources her Department has allocated to the Wales Extremism and Counter Terrorism Unit in 2014-15; and what changes to those resources are expected in (a) 2015-16, (b) 2016-17 and (c) 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","1823"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349796","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-15","<p>The first phase of the Contract for Difference negotiation for the Swansea Bay tidal lagoon project enables the Department to better understand the potential of a tidal lagoon programme in the UK.</p><p>We recognise the need to consider the strategic case for having multiple tidal lagoons in the Severn Estuary and the impact that this could have on the area.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-06-15T14:33:39.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349796/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349796/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349796/answer",,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-06-10","Severn Estuary: Tidal Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what impact assessment the Government has made of proposals for further tidal lagoons in the Severn Estuary.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","1824"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349797","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-22","<p>Statistics on employee expenditure in each local authority are published online in the Revenue Outturn Service Expenditure Summary, which is available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/collections/local-authority-revenue-expenditure-and-financing" target="_blank">http://www.gov.uk/government/collections/local-authority-revenue-expenditure-and-financing</a></p><p> </p><p>Data is not currently available for 2014-15.</p><p> </p><p>This Department does not hold centrally the level of member’s remuneration by local authority.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2015-06-22T15:15:20.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349797/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349797/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349797/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-10","Local Government: Cumbria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what information his Department holds on how much was spent on (a) staffing and (b) members' remuneration by each local authority area in Cumbria in (i) 2012-13, (ii) 2013-14 and (iii) 2014-15.","false","Biography information for John Stevenson","Carlisle","John Stevenson","1835"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349798","Department of Health","false","2015-06-15","<p>Early diagnosis of cancer is a major priority for this Government in helping us to improve cancer survival.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The NHS Cervical Screening Programme in England offers screening to women aged 50 to 64 every five years to help detect and treat any cervical abnormalities at an early stage. Public Health England continues to work with NHS England to develop a system of performance improvement to increase screening coverage amongst all eligible age groups, particularly in disadvantaged communities. We fully support efforts to warn women aged 50 to 64 about the risks of missing their appointments, as it is important that women above vaccination age realise that cervical screening is the best way to prevent cervical cancer.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In April 2012 the UK National Screening Committee (UK NSC) gave its support for a pilot to assess the value of using human papilloma virus (HPV) testing as primary screening for cervical disease, rather than the currently used cytology test. The pilot is establishing the feasibility of using HPV as the primary screen for cervical disease in order to achieve better outcomes for women, while minimising over-treatment and anxiety, and whether it is practical to roll out nationally. The UK NSC will open a public consultation shortly on whether HPV as primary screening for cervical disease should replace the currently used cytology test.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence is in the process of updating the “Referral Guidelines for Suspected Cancer” (2005) to ensure that it reflects latest evidence and can continue to support general practitioners (GPs) to identify patients with the symptoms of suspected cancer, including gynaecological cancers and urgently refer them as appropriate. Women under 25 who are concerned about their risk of developing cervical cancer should contact their GP.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>A cervical screening test is primarily used for screening purposes, and is unlikely to be appropriate when a woman has gynaecological issues that are symptomatic of cancer.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>When a woman is experiencing gynaecological problems which are symptomatic of gynaecological cancer, their GP would be expected to refer them to the appropriate specialist without needing to conduct a screening test.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","1501","2015-06-15T15:31:55.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349798/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349798/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349798/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-10","Cervical Cancer: Older People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department is taking to reduce the number of women over the age of 50 being diagnosed with advanced stage cervical cancer.","false","Biography information for Mark Durkan","Foyle","Mark Durkan","1833"
