"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349345","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-16","<p>The Government introduced the EU Referendum Bill to the House of Commons on 28 May 2015. The franchise for the referendum is based on the longstanding UK Parliamentary franchise, with the addition of Members of the House of Lords and Commonwealth citizens in Gibraltar. This is an issue of national significance, so it is appropriate that the UK Parliamentary franchise is used.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2015-06-16T14:12:33.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349345/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349345/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349345/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-09","UK Membership of EU: Referendums","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will conduct a public consultation on the franchise for the referendum on membership of the EU.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","1525"
