"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349387","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-15","<p>Estimates of the number of taxpayers in each income tax rate band broken down by country and region are published in HM Revenue &amp; Custom's National Statistics table 2.2 which is available on the internet at the following address:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/429136/Table_2.2.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/429136/Table_2.2.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-06-15T16:54:56.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349387/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349387/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349387/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-09","Taxation: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people in Wales paid tax at (a) basic, (b) higher and (c) additional tax bands in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","1701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349388","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-18","<p>The Chancellor of the Exchequer has frequent discussions with the Governor of the Bank of England on a wide range of issues on the UK economy.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In addition to these discussions, after the publication of each Financial Stability Report the Chancellor and the Governor of the Bank of England are required by the Bank of England Act 1998 (as amended by the Financial Services Act 2012) to meet to discuss the Report and other matters related to financial stability. The minutes of the meeting held to discuss the December 2014 FSR were published on HM Treasury’s website and can be found at the following website link.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/record-of-financial-stability-report-meeting-february-2015</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-06-18T11:09:41.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349388/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349388/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349388/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-09","Economic Growth","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent discussions he has had with the Governor of the Bank of England about promoting economic growth and financial stability across the whole of the UK.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","1702"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349389","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-15","<p>Great Western electrification is the biggest and most complex electrification scheme for more than a generation, passing through several World Heritage sites and involving around 15,000 foundations, 14,000 masts, 1,500 signal upgrades and 50 station improvements. Network Rail continues to work towards delivering electrification to agreed timescales.</p><p> </p><p>This is an extremely challenging programme and we are working closely with Network Rail and the Office of Rail and Road (ORR) to ensure successful delivery. However, I would reiterate that it is this Government which is working hard on rail electrification compared to the performance of the previous Labour government which managed to electrify just 10 miles over their entire 13 years in office. In addition, in the previous Parliament we also agreed a funding package to deliver the electrification of the Welsh Valley lines.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-06-15T12:46:24.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349389/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349389/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349389/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-09","Great Western Railway Line: Electrification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he expects the electrification of the Great Western Line between London and Swansea will be completed.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","1703"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349390","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-16","<p>The UK's participation in the July UN Open-Ended Working Group on Ageing is being coordinated across Whitehall by the Foreign and Commonwealth Office. The UK will be represented by delegates based in the UK Mission to New York. We will also field a UK expert to take part in the panel discussion on “Ageing in Cities”. We are working closely with EU partners on preparation for the meeting, and have ensured that UK policy is reflected in the EU contribution on proposals to strengthen the protection of the rights of older people. The UK will also contribute to EU statements on each of the panel sessions.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2015-06-16T13:57:33.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349390/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349390/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349390/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-09","UN Open-ended Working Group on Ageing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what preparations his Department has made for the upcoming UN Open-Ended Working Group on Ageing.","false","Biography information for Heidi Alexander","Lewisham East","Heidi Alexander","1606"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349391","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-15","<p /> <p>The information requested is not available. In order to be eligible to receive state benefits, eligibility conditions usually require a claimant to be resident in the United Kingdom. Claimants are required to tell DWP if they leave the country to travel abroad, but we do not keep records regarding the country a person is travelling to.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-06-15T13:21:31.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349391/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349391/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349391/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-09","Social Security Benefits: Arab States","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what (a) number and (b) total amount of benefit payments have been received by people living in (i) Iraq and (ii) Syria in (A) 2012, (B) 2013, (C) 2014 and (D) 2015 to date.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","1648"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349392","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-23","<p>In South Suffolk constituency commercial broadband delivery is estimated to cover 19,252 (45%) of homes and businesses. By the end of the Better Broadband for Suffolk project, coverage is expected to have increased to over 36,800 (86%) of premises.</p><p> </p><p>In the Better Broadband for Suffolk project over 117,000 homes and businesses across the county will benefit from public investment. As of March 2015, the project had already reached over 70,600 premises.</p><p> </p><p>The Department deposited data in the House of Commons Library which estimates commercial coverage and coverage supported by public investment in constituencies by the end of 2017. The table can be found here: <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/business-papers/commons/deposited-papers/?house=1&amp;search_term=Department+for+Culture%2c+Media+and+Sport&amp;itemId=122028#toggle-163" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/business-papers/commons/deposited-papers/?house=1&amp;search_term=Department+for+Culture%2c+Media+and+Sport&amp;itemId=122028#toggle-163 </a></p><p> </p><p>The Department does not monitor roll-out at constituency level. However, Ofcom publishes annual data on coverage at county level. The following data taken from Ofcom Infrastructure Reports indicates coverage in Suffolk between 2012 and 2014. Ofcom calculated 2012-14 coverage figures using different methodologies and in 2014 produced two sets of figures. Further details can be found on the Ofcom website: <a href="http://maps.ofcom.org.uk/" target="_blank">http://maps.ofcom.org.uk/</a></p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>County</p></td><td><p>Proportion of households in postcodes served by NGA networks</p><p>2012</p></td><td><p>Proportion of premises in postcodes served by NGA networks 2013</p></td><td><p>Proportion of premises able to receive NGA broadband services 2014</p></td><td><p>Availability of superfast broadband (30+Mbit/s) 2014</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Suffolk</p></td><td><p>45%</p></td><td><p>59%</p></td><td><p>68%</p></td><td><p>64%</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-06-23T14:42:02.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349392/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349392/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349392/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-09","Broadband: South Suffolk","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many additional premises in South Suffolk constituency were connected to high speed broadband services in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for James Cartlidge","South Suffolk","James Cartlidge","1608"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349393","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-15","<p /> <p>The new statutory duty will require the Secretary of State to publish an annual report on progress towards full employment. This duty will not impact on existing responsibilities of the Welsh Government to develop and deliver employment related policies. We will be engaging with the Devolved Administrations in due course.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-06-15T13:57:25.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349393/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349393/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349393/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-09","Employment: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent discussions he has had with the Welsh Government on creating a duty to report on progress towards full employment.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","1689"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349394","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-16","<p /> <p><strong> </strong></p><p>Detailed housing benefit statistics, including those aged 18 to 21 in Wales by number of dependent children, can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk</a></p><p> </p><p>Guidance on how to extract the information required can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started---SuperWEB2.html" target="_blank">https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started---SuperWEB2.html</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Information on those households receiving housing benefit and containing someone registered as disabled is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>The information requested for those who have previously been in local authority care is not collected on the data available for analysis and therefore is not available.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-16T13:30:27.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349394/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349394/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349394/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-09","Housing Benefit: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many young people aged 18 to 21 in Wales receive housing benefit; how many such people (a) have children, (b) are disabled and (c) have previously been in local authority care.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","1690"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349395","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-15","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 8 June 2015 to Questions <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=QuestionsWithAnswersOnly&amp;house=commons,lords&amp;use-dates=True&amp;answered-from=2015-06-08&amp;answered-to=2015-06-08&amp;uin=887" target="_blank">UIN 887</a> and <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=QuestionsWithAnswersOnly&amp;house=commons,lords&amp;use-dates=True&amp;answered-from=2015-06-08&amp;answered-to=2015-06-08&amp;uin=889" target="_blank">UIN 889</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-06-15T14:24:35.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349395/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349395/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349395/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-09","Unemployment Benefits: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many young people in Wales will be eligible for the Youth Allowance.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","1691"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349396","Home Office","false","2015-06-16","<p>The Home Office does not hold the data requested. While all four Welsh police forces contributed to the police response to the consultation on pre-charge bail issued in November 2014, that response only covers April 2013 to March 2014 and is not broken down by force. Estimated annual figures for the whole of England and Wales are set out on page 25 of the Government response to the consultation, published on 23 March and available at: https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/pre-charge-bail-consultation-on-statutory-time-limits-and-related-changes.</p><p>As part of the Government’s reforms announced on 23 March, all forces will be required to collect data on pre-charge bail to ensure transparency and public accountability. The Government will also legislate in the Police Reform and Criminal Justice Bill to adopt the model endorsed by the consultation, in which pre-charge bail is initially limited at 28 days, with extension of up to three months able to be authorised by a senior police officer in complex cases.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-06-16T14:57:35.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349396/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349396/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349396/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-06-09","Bail: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people have been on bail without charge by police forces in Wales for more than (a) 28 days and (b) three months in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","1692"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349397","Home Office","false","2015-06-12","<p>Figure 1 shows the number of complaints cases recorded in each of the Welsh police forces for the latest 5-year period currently available. Data on the number of officers suspended in each force is not collected centrally.</p><p>Figure 2 shows College of Policing data on the number of officers leaving the police due to misconduct by rank from 1 December 2013 to 30 November 2014. The statistics relate to all 43 forces in England and Wales as well as the British Transport Police and Ministry of Defence Police. The Home Office does not have a break-down of this data by individual police force.</p><p>Out of the 444 cases, a total of 405 (91%) came from internal complaints and investiga-tions, while 39 (9%) came from complaints by members of the public.</p><p>The Home Office will publish details of misconduct outcomes, with an individual force break-down, from 2016 as part of a new annual data return. These statistics relate to a period before the Home Office introduced legislation in January to stop officers resigning or retiring in cases that could lead to dismissal. Where an allegation is received from 12 January 2015 officers will only be able to retire or resign with the consent of the chief officer in exceptional circumstances. The Police and Criminal Justice Bill will be introduced in this Parliament so that investigations and misconduct hearings can be concluded against officers even after they have resigned or retired. Any officer that would have been dismissed will be struck-off from involvement in any future policing activity.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-06-12T13:58:08.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349397/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349397/answer","PQ1693 Fig1[2].doc ; PQ 1693 Fig2[1].doc","PQ1693 Fig1[2].doc ; PQ 1693 Fig2[1].doc","Complaint cases recorded by year ; Police officers leaving due to misconduct","Complaint cases recorded by year ; Police officers leaving due to misconduct","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349397/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-06-09","Police: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many complaints have been made against each of the police forces in Wales in each of the last five years; and how many officers have been (a) suspended and (b) dismissed for misconduct in each force.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","1693"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349398","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-15","<p>Ministers and senior officials in my Department are engaging on an ongoing basis with lenders and other financial institutions in relation to key policy issues.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-06-15T14:30:08.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349398/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349398/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349398/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-09","Right to Buy Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what discussions he has had with mortgage lenders on the implications for lending of an extension of the right to buy to housing association tenants.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","1650"
